"Abstract Ulrich Sieber continues with the second part of his report on the legal issues of liability for Internet service providers. This section completes this legal analysis of sec. 5 of the German Teleservices Act which provides a graduated system of responsibility for the different parties involved. He then goes on to discuss the technical basics of network technology and deals with a number of misconceptions about the control possibilities of the Internet. This section is a precursor to Part III which will consider technical control measures."
